    <main><div class='container-fluid' id='dict_container'>
      <h1><span class='badge badge-primary'>volatile keyword in C++</span></h1>
      <div class='container-fluid'>
          <pre id='word_content' style='white-space: pre-wrap;'>According to the C++11 ISO Standard, the volatile keyword is only meant for use for hardware access; do not use it for inter-thread communication. For inter-thread communication, the standard library provides std::atomic&lt;T&gt; templates.
```
#include &lt;csignal&gt;
#include &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

volatile sig_atomic_t gSignalStatus;

void signal_handler(int signal) {
  gSignalStatus = signal;
}

int main() {
  signal(SIGINT, signal_handler);

  cout &lt;&lt; &quot;SignalValue: &quot; &lt;&lt; gSignalStatus &lt;&lt; endl;
  cout &lt;&lt; &quot;Sending signal &quot; &lt;&lt; SIGINT &lt;&lt; endl;
  raise(SIGINT);
  cout &lt;&lt; &quot;SignalValue: &quot; &lt;&lt; gSignalStatus &lt;&lt; endl;
}
```</pre>
